commit bfb20be9ffef57a227ebba126873a41f721eb9cc
Author: Jure Varlec <jure.varlec@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jan 20 15:23:18 2010 +0100

    Adds graceful termination, SIGINT handling and optional ksharrays.
    
    Handler is only in the shell; it seems SIGINT interrupts the subshell,
    not the jobserver, so the shell always receives the signal. Further
    testing is required to determine whether this is fully robust, although
    timing the signal to arrive while the jobserver is running will be tricky.

